description.narrative: Positive progresses in 2019 include: i) the development and initial implementation in 9 schools of a key elements of the school drop-out prevention programme, including the new online early warning system to identify children at risk of dropping-out based on school administrative data; and ongoing testing of WASH in schools models (soft and hardware) in 34 schools for approximately 10,000 children; and ii) the finalization of all preparatory steps to implement the second chance programme for children having dropped-out of schools in 2 centres operated by public and private sectors respectively, with a strong multi-sector partnership built at national level. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:21/01/2020
